{
  "id": "phase-rs_phase_1669",
  "repo_name": "phase-rs/phase",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/phase-rs/phase",
  "base_commit": "5f9eb171b39cc4a5ce48ad0996de349f691f4465",
  "pr_number": 1669,
  "issue_number": 1666,
  "issue_title": "Vanguard of the Restless: anthem scaling with commander casts from command zone resolves to +0/+0",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n**Vanguard of the Restless**'s anthem \u2014 *\"Spirits you control get +1/+1 for each time you've cast your commander from the command zone this game\"* \u2014 does not appear to buff your Spirits. The P/T bonus reads as 0 even after the commander has been cast from the command zone.\n\n## Card\n\n**Vanguard of the Restless** (SOC)\n\n> Flying\n> Spirits you control get +1/+1 for each time you've cast your commander from the command zone this game.\n> Whenever a Spirit you control enters, you may pay {2}{W}. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield.\n\n## Expected\n\nPer the static ability, each Spirit you control (including Vanguard itself) gets +N/+N where N is the number of times you've cast your commander from the command zone this game (CR 903.8 cast-count semantics). Per the printed rulings, the count includes casts that were countered or are still on the stack.\n\n## Actual\n\nSpirits receive no bonus \u2014 the modification resolves to +0/+0 in practice.\n\n## What is verified to be correct (NOT the bug)\n\nThis is a **runtime resolution** problem, not a parser misparse. The pipeline below is all present and correct:\n\n1. **Parse** (`data/card-data.json`): the static ability parses correctly into:\n   ```\n   AddDynamicPower    { value: Ref(CommanderCastFromCommandZoneCount) }\n   AddDynamicToughness{ value: Ref(CommanderCastFromCommandZoneCount) }\n   ```\n   affecting `Creature + Subtype(Spirit), controller: You`.\n2. **Layer application** (`crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs:3306-3315`): layer 7c (CR 613.4c) applies `AddDynamicPower`/`AddDynamicToughness` from a precomputed `dynamic_pt`, resolved via `resolve_quantity(...)` at `layers.rs:2978`.\n3. **Quantity resolution** (`crates/engine/src/game/quantity.rs:1698`): `CommanderCastFromCommandZoneCount` \u2192 `commander::commander_casts_from_command_zone(state, controller)`.\n4. **Cast tracking** (`crates/engine/src/game/casting_costs.rs:3268-3271`): `record_commander_cast` fires when `was_in_command_zone` is true, so countered / on-stack casts are counted (matches rulings).\n\n## Leading hypothesis (for the investigator)\n\n`commander_casts_from_command_zone` (`crates/engine/src/game/commander.rs:27-39`) does not read the count map directly. It iterates `state.commander_cast_count` and **re-validates each recorded key against live `state.objects`**:\n\n```rust\n.filter(|(commander_id, _)| {\n    state.objects.get(commander_id)\n        .is_some_and(|obj| obj.is_commander && obj.owner == player)\n})\n```\n\n`commander_cast_count` is keyed by the `ObjectId` recorded at cast time (the command-zone/stack object). If that `ObjectId` no longer resolves to a live `is_commander && owner == player` object when Vanguard's static is evaluated \u2014 e.g. because object identity is not preserved across the command-zone \u2192 stack \u2192 battlefield transition, or because the commander has changed zones since \u2014 the recorded entry is silently dropped and the sum is 0.\n\nContrast with **commander tax** (`commander.rs:11-18`), which reads `commander_cast_count.get(&commander_id)` directly by id and therefore works regardless of the object's current zone/state. The divergence between these two readers of the same map is the suspicious part.\n\nThe existing test (`quantity.rs:4067-4112`) only exercises the case where the recorded commander objects remain in `state.objects` with `is_commander == true`, so it would not catch an id-survival mismatch in the real cast\u2192resolve flow.\n\n## Suggested investigation\n\n- Add an end-to-end test: cast a real commander from the command zone, resolve it to the battlefield, then evaluate `commander_casts_from_command_zone` \u2014 confirm it returns 1, not 0.\n- If the recorded `ObjectId` doesn't survive zone changes, key the count by a stable identity (owner + commander identity) rather than the transient object id, matching whatever makes commander tax stable across recasts.\n\n## Scope (build for the class, not the card)\n\n`CommanderCastFromCommandZoneCount` is a reusable `QuantityRef` building block. Fixing the counter correctly benefits every current and future card that scales off commander casts, not just Vanguard of the Restless.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-31T16:13:27.000Z",
